content:
When support agents work with cases in Case Feed, they use the case page layout. To specify the fields, tools, and functionality that support agents see when working with open cases, customize the feed view, detail view, highlights panel in the case page.

You can also customize the close case page layout. Highlights panels show key information about a case so that the most important information is immediately visible to agents.

Feed views show the case history using a Chatter-like feed, so that agents can see what's happened in a case in context. Detail views show useful information about the case, such as a description of the contact's company and related lists.

You can customize the close case page layout which appears when agents close cases. This lets them enter information about the case resolution.

From object management settings for cases, you can create, edit, and assign all four types of layouts by going to Page Layouts.

The highlights panel can be edited to include the fields that are most important for your support agents. The Case Feed publisher can also be configured with the enhanced page layout editor.

Feed view page layouts determine which actions, fields, and tools users see when working with cases in Case Feed. You can create different layouts and assign them to different user profiles.

Custom feed filters can help support agents focus on the items that are most relevant for them.
title: Service Cloud: Configuring Case Feed Page Layouts
